OER Connector -- Connecting the World to the Education Commons.

A chromium extension connecting people to oercommons.org.

OER Connector is licensed under a MIT License. See LICENSE for details.

To install OER Connector, please follow these instructions:

* Download the latest version from here: http://github.com/sdziallas/oer-connector/zipball/master
* Unpack the resulting file in a directory.
* Open Chromium and bring the extensions screen up by clicking on the tools menu in the top right corner.
* Click on Developer Mode and Load an unpacked Extension.
* Select the directory you created above in the file dialog and click OK to load the OER Connector extension.

Setup your own server:

* Copy submit.php and data.txt rom the backend directory to a publically accessible place.
* Open manifest.json and adjust the domain name in line 11.
* Change the direct URL to the submit.php script in line 39 of the popup.html file.
* Reload the extension and you should be good to go.

(Brought to you by Team OER Ninja!)
